==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rutin
<hw>Ru"tin</hw> <pr>(r⟦udd⟧"t⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A glucoside resembling, but distinct from,
quercitrin. Rutin is found in the leaves of the rue (<spn>Ruta
graveolens</spn>) and other plants, and obtained as a bitter yellow
crystalline substance which yields quercitin on decomposition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rutinose.</ent>⟦br⟧
